image_list.title: Margaret Lanterman
image_list.subtitle_html: Log Lady
image_list.gallery_page_teaser: Margaret Lanterman's spiritual portrait shows she is outgoing and can be amiable, but cares only about ideas, and not at all about facts.  Click on the image to learn more!
image_list.explain_dom: The Blue in this spiritual portrait represents Margaret's dominant personality trait, iNtuition: idealism and hope for the future; openness to ideas; very slight/moderate/strong preference for ideas over facts.
The Blue in Margaret's spiritual portrait represents their dominant personality trait, their very slight/moderate/strong preference for seeing the world more in terms of ideas than of facts.
image_list.explain_dom_constant: In Extraverts, the dominant trait is directed outwardly, and spiritual portraits use a long vertical line to represent this, because it is the side of their personality that is most evident. The Red in Margaret's spiritual portrait represents their auxiliary personality trait, their very slight/moderate/strong preference for making emotional/personal/objective rather than logical/rational/subjective decisions; their very slight/moderate/strong preference for making emotional/personal/subjective decisions.
